data.title: Music rags and papers
data.meta_description:
I’ve always loved music and as a lad in the UK I was subscribed to… 
 
Melody Maker and Sounds Mag got a look in too, where did you pre Web get your sounds info from?
data.text:
WLIR, Long Island Radio was a NYC ish radio station, which on a good day you could tune into on the Jersey side of the Hudson. Some times I would park my car on the Palisades just so I could tune in. You could get certain college stations in the radius of a few blocks but back in the day This was the only real radio station for new music in the entire NYC area.
